TY  - JOUR
AU  - Pan, Yihui
AU  - Wang, Tracy Yue
AU  - Weisbach, Michael S.
T1  - Learning About CEO Ability and Stock Return Volatility
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/06/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhv014
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 28
IS  - 6
SP  - 1623
EP  - 1666
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Consistent with predictions from a stylized Bayesian learning model stock return volatility declines with CEO tenure in a convex manner, even for CEOs whose appointments occur for exogenous reasons. The decline is faster when there is higher uncertainty about the CEO's ability when there is more transparency about the firm's prospects, and when CEO ability is more important in value creation. We quantify the importance of uncertainty about CEO ability relative to the firm's fundamental cash flow uncertainty in contributing to stock return volatility, highlighting the importance of management in creating value.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhv014
ER  - 



